'''FC Barcelona Femenino''' is a [[Spain|Spanish]] women's football team from [[Barcelona, Spain|Barcelona]] founded as '''Club FemenÃ­ Barcelona''' in the 1980s. It is the women's section of [[FC Barcelona]].

CF Barcelona, which was sponsored by FC Barcelona, was a founder member of the [[Superliga Femenina|Spanish League]] in 1988, and won the 1994 [[Copa de la Reina]]. In 2001 it was incorporated to FC Barcelona as an official section as the Spanish League was refounded into the Superliga Femenina. The team has took part in the Superliga every season except for the 2007-08. In 2011 the team won the Spanish Cup a second time.<ref>{{cite web|title=FC Barcelona, campeÃ³n de la Copa de SM La Reina tras vencer al RCD Espanyol (1-0)|url=http://www.rfef.es/index.jsp?nodo=119&ID=1479|publisher=rfef.es|accessdate=19 June 2011|language=Spanish|date=19 June 2011}}</ref> 

On August 30, 2009, it won its second title, the 2009 [[Copa Catalunya]].

==Honours== 
* '''[[Copa de la Reina]] (2)''': 1994, 2011
** runners-up: 1991
* '''[[Copa Catalunya]] (3)''': 2009, 2010, 2011

